                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5433.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Vera Cruz</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-07T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Profuse expressions of friendship for the United States are being made by
                    citizens and residents of the State and city of Vera Cruz; Commander Hughes is
                    virtually their hero now, and he is entitled to all the praise and credit given
                    him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
